<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">310.393/6–451: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-04T18:00:00-04:00">June 4,
                                    1951—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5637. Pls deliver fol personal msg from SecState to Morrison:</p>
                        <p>“I shld like to express my appreciation for your reply to my msg on the
                            Chi representation question in the <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>,
                            which has been delivered by Reps of the Brit <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> here.</p>
                        <p>“I am certain that, thru advance consultation between our Reps along the
                            lines on which we are now agreed, we can successfully dispose of this
                            issue when it is raised in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> bodies
                            without undue difficulty and without an undesirable and repeated airing
                            of our differing views.</p>
                        <p>“The position we shall now jointly support will be very helpful to us
                            here and will I know be well received by public opinion in this
                            country.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>